	<div class="article-detail-bd">
			<div class="excerpt">
				火爆的原因是够便宜。
			</div>
		<div class="detail">
				<!-- 普通文章 -->
				<p class="MsoNormal">
	<a href="http://www.wired.com/2012/10/ff-elon-musk-qa/" target="_blank">2026&nbsp;</a><span style="font-family:宋体;"><a href="http://www.wired.com/2012/10/ff-elon-musk-qa/" target="_blank">年前在火星上建立第一个殖民地</a></span><span style="font-family:宋体;">，这是&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">SpaceX&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">创始人&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Elon&nbsp;Musk&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">念叨了多年的计划，具体来说就是造出适合火星之旅的发动机、实现火箭回收再利用技术以降低成本，然后，出发。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	尽管&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">SpaceX&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的猎户座&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">9&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号飞船最近已经<a href="http://www.theverge.com/2015/4/14/8406063/spacex-falcon-9-barge-landing-attempt-fails" target="_blank">第&nbsp;</a></span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';"><a href="http://www.theverge.com/2015/4/14/8406063/spacex-falcon-9-barge-landing-attempt-fails" target="_blank">N&nbsp;</a></span><span style="font-family:宋体;"><a href="http://www.theverge.com/2015/4/14/8406063/spacex-falcon-9-barge-landing-attempt-fails" target="_blank">次回收失败</a></span><span style="font-family:宋体;">了，但在&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Musk&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的带动下，私人公司进入太空领域渐渐成了一件时髦的事情，昨天<a href="http://qdaily.com/display/articles/8593.html" target="_blank">《好奇心日报》就报道</a>了</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">私人公司&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Rocket&nbsp;Lab&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">要造电动火箭的消息。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	事实上，向近地轨道发射火箭和卫星开始变成一门越来越火爆的生意。不管是波音这样的巨头，还是微软的联合创始人&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Paul Allen&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">以及维珍航空&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">CEO&nbsp;Richard&nbsp;Branson&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">爵士，他们都在涌进这项预估年产值可达&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">19&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">亿美元的产业。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><img src="http://media.gotraffic.net/images/iicUwP5i7Cdo/v3/750x-1.jpg" alt="" /><br />
</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:center;">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><em>近十年每年卫星发射的数量（图片来源：</em><a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-13/forget-musk-s-mars-billionaires-branson-allen-seek-earth-orbit" target="_blank"><em>彭博社</em></a><em>）</em><em></em></span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	据咨询公司&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Teal&nbsp;Group&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的数据，</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2014&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年发射的卫星达到了&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">303&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">颗，是以往年份的近两倍，且仍有价值近&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">亿美元的商用卫星发射还在排队等候。而&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2011&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年才成立的&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';"><a href="http://www.generationorbit.com/" target="_blank">Generation&nbsp;Orbit&nbsp;</a></span><span style="font-family:宋体;"><a href="http://www.generationorbit.com/" target="_blank">卫星发射服务公司</a>&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">COO&nbsp;Piplica&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">称他们今年收到了&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">10&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">封意向书，预计每年将发射&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">200&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">到&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">250&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">颗卫星。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	Teal&nbsp;Group&nbsp;<span style="font-family:宋体;">的太空研究负责人&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Marco&nbsp;Caceres&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">在<a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-13/forget-musk-s-mars-billionaires-branson-allen-seek-earth-orbit" target="_blank">接受彭博社采访时称</a></span><span style="font-family:宋体;">：“这是未来的趋势，哪怕有人说我们将看到一年发射几千颗卫星，这也不是什么疯话。”</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	更重要的是卫星发射的成本也在下降，原先美国公司用俄罗斯的第聂伯号（<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Dnepr</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">）运载火箭“搭便车”发射商业卫星的费用是&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">1200&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">万美元，而且还得按着火箭的发射时间表等候。</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	Rocket&nbsp;Lab&nbsp;<span style="font-family:宋体;">研发的轻型火箭兴许能在&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2016&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年让发射收费降低到&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">490&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">万美元，</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Generation&nbsp;Orbit&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">则在努力接近&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">200&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">万美元，而波音未来的报价更是可能低于&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">100&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">万美元。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	为了节约成本，这些公司的新办法层出不穷——当然&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Musk&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">那至今没成功的“回收火箭大法”还是太难。</span> 
</p>
<h2>
	“小而美”才省钱
</h2>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	如今越来越多被发射上天的商用卫星都是&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">1&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">万美元左右的小卫星，重量最低的也只有&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">1&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">千克，作用一般是监控农作物、创建互联网热点连接或者追踪天气等。发射这类卫星用大功率运载火箭，实在有点“杀鸡用牛刀”的即视感，而且这类商用卫星的发射一般是作为大火箭的第二载荷“捎带”上去的，发射时间得根据大火箭的安排来，往往一等就是一两年。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	为此，目前大部分商业卫星发射公司都在开发轻型火箭。<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Rocket&nbsp;Lab&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的火箭只有&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">18&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">米高，是俄罗斯第聂伯号火箭的一半。而且&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Rocket&nbsp;Lab&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">也放弃在佛罗里达州肯尼迪航天中心发射火箭，而是选在南半球的新西兰，可选的轨道角度更大，同时——也更便宜。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	当然还有更小的火箭，不过这就不是在地上发射的了。<o:p></o:p>
</p>
<h2>
	&nbsp;与其回收，不如从飞机上发射火箭
</h2>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	用飞机发射火箭则是波音、<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Generation&nbsp;Orbit&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">等公司能做到更低价的法宝。</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;">飞机上发射的都是更小型的火箭，比如波音公司正在研发的用于飞机上发射的火箭只有&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">7&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">米多一点点高，这严格说来只能算是火箭的最后一节。</span>它的省钱原理其实和火箭回收类似，毕竟发射火箭的飞机可以多次使用，就相当于回收了正常火箭的前几级。
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	和地面发射后再回收相比，飞机发射的技术难度会小很多。这其实和发射一枚导弹一样，像波音公司用的飞机就是&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">F-15E&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">战斗机；当然战斗机也不是所有公司都买得到，</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Generation&nbsp;Orbit 则</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">使用了湾流</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">公司</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">（</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Gulfstream</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">）</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">生产的“湾流”客机。</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Lockheed_TriStar_launches_Pegasus_with_Space_Technology_5.jpg/800px-Lockheed_TriStar_launches_Pegasus_with_Space_Technology_5.jpg" alt="" /><br />
</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:center;">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><em>用湾流客机发射</em><span style="white-space:normal;"><em>小型火箭</em></span></span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	此外，微软联合创始人&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Paul Allen&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">也成立了&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Stratolaunch&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">项目研究在平流层发射火箭的技术。昨日，</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Allen&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Vulcan&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">集团<a href="http://www.space.com/29117-vulcan-aerospace-paul-allen-private-spaceflight.html" target="_blank">又宣布</a></span><a href="http://www.space.com/29117-vulcan-aerospace-paul-allen-private-spaceflight.html" target="_blank"><span style="font-family:宋体;">成立新的&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Vulcan&nbsp;Aerospace&nbsp;</span></a><span style="font-family:宋体;"><a href="http://www.space.com/29117-vulcan-aerospace-paul-allen-private-spaceflight.html" target="_blank">公司</a>，计划制造世界上最大的飞机用于发射火箭。新飞机的翼展将达到&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">117&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">米，比空客&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">A380&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">还长 37 米</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">，拥有&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">6&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">个引擎，预计会在&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2016&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年进入测试阶段。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	维珍航空&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">CEO&nbsp;Richard&nbsp;Branson&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">创立的维珍银河（</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Virgin&nbsp;Galactic</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">）则会使用自己制造的“火箭飞机”：“白骑士&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号”（</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">WhiteKnightTwo</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">），它个体比&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">Stratolaunch&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">的小，也只有&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">4&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">个引擎。</span><o:p></o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6a/WhiteKnight_Two_flying.jpg" width="640" height="427" alt="" /><br />
</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:center;">
	<em>白骑士 2 号</em><em>，图片来自：</em><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scaled_Composites_White_Knight_Two" target="_blank"><em>Wikipedia</em></a> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	但“白骑士&nbsp;<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2014&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年就已投入使用，搭载过“太空船&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号”以测试未来的豪华太空游。不过在那次试验中，“太空船&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号”分离不久便坠毁，导致一名飞行员不幸丧生。进入卫星发射领域后，</span><span style="font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;">预计</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">“白骑士&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">号”将在&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';">2016&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family:宋体;">年测试全新的发射技术。</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;"><br />
</span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<span style="font-family:宋体;">题图来自：<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Launch_vehicle" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a></span> 
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">
	<o:p></o:p>
</p>
		</div>
